1
00:00:02,419 --> 00:00:04,713
I’m going to ask you a few questions now.

2
00:00:04,963 --> 00:00:10,176
Just put on the VR headset in front of you and answer comfortably.

3
00:00:38,621 --> 00:00:39,748
Whoa.

4
00:00:41,082 --> 00:00:43,001
You see the test app on the screen?

5
00:00:43,793 --> 00:00:46,588
Can you tap that and go in?

6
00:00:46,588 --> 00:00:48,757
Yeah, I’m in.

7
00:00:48,965 --> 00:00:52,552
I’ll be recording your eye movements and facial expressions.

8
00:00:53,303 --> 00:00:54,095
Huh?

9
00:00:54,971 --> 00:00:56,765
I can’t see anything now.

10
00:00:57,599 --> 00:00:59,559
Then let’s begin.

11
00:01:01,186 --> 00:01:03,313
Okay.

12
00:01:04,481 --> 00:01:07,817
Test subject, Case-Delphi, starting questionnaire.

13
00:01:07,817 --> 00:01:10,779
This experiment is to measure emotional responses.

14
00:01:10,779 --> 00:01:13,239
All answers will be recorded via the VR device.

15
00:01:13,239 --> 00:01:15,492
A variety of questions will be presented.

16
00:01:15,492 --> 00:01:17,702
Please let me know if you feel uncomfortable at any point.

17
00:01:17,952 --> 00:01:19,496
Got it.

18
00:01:20,747 --> 00:01:22,582
How are you feeling right now?

19
00:01:23,291 --> 00:01:25,001
A little nervous.

20
00:01:26,002 --> 00:01:28,046
Alright, we’ll proceed.

21
00:01:28,588 --> 00:01:30,423
Are you currently seeing anyone?

22
00:01:30,548 --> 00:01:31,633
No.

23
00:01:32,092 --> 00:01:32,967
Hmm…

24
00:01:33,802 --> 00:01:36,054
Then is there someone you like?

25
00:01:37,847 --> 00:01:39,015
Yes.

26
00:01:43,186 --> 00:01:48,274
Can you name three things you have in common with that person?

27
00:01:49,067 --> 00:01:51,569
Uh…

28
00:01:51,569 --> 00:01:53,363
Good at studying.

29
00:01:53,363 --> 00:01:55,782
Kind.

30
00:01:55,782 --> 00:01:58,368
And if you really get to know them… kind of scary?

31
00:02:02,080 --> 00:02:03,623
Those are common traits, right?

32
00:02:04,374 --> 00:02:06,709
Yes, they are.

33
00:02:07,210 --> 00:02:10,964
What are you most grateful for in your life?

34
00:02:12,090 --> 00:02:12,882
I…

35
00:02:13,967 --> 00:02:16,970
I used to be really off track.

36
00:02:17,387 --> 00:02:22,308
I didn’t listen to my parents, gave up on studying…

37
00:02:22,308 --> 00:02:23,268
But…

38
00:02:23,852 --> 00:02:26,813
Someone held onto me back then.

39
00:02:26,813 --> 00:02:30,817
Even when I was hopeless, they didn’t let go.

40
00:02:36,072 --> 00:02:39,242
If you could change one thing about your childhood,

41
00:02:40,493 --> 00:02:43,997
what would it be?

42
00:02:51,588 --> 00:02:58,344
I wish I hadn’t confessed to that person so recklessly.

43
00:03:10,106 --> 00:03:11,024
Hyung—

44
00:03:11,441 --> 00:03:13,318
I mean… teacher—

45
00:03:13,860 --> 00:03:16,738
Do you have a girlfriend?

46
00:03:17,739 --> 00:03:20,283
Focus on studying.

47
00:03:21,451 --> 00:03:24,204
If you tell me, I will.

48
00:03:26,497 --> 00:03:27,916
What do you think?

49
00:03:29,667 --> 00:03:31,002
Probably yes.

50
00:03:31,544 --> 00:03:34,714
You go to a good school, you’re tall, handsome…

51
00:03:35,715 --> 00:03:37,800
No, I don’t.

52
00:03:37,800 --> 00:03:39,928
Do you like someone?

53
00:03:41,846 --> 00:03:43,056
Uh…

54
00:03:44,015 --> 00:03:45,975
I think so.

55
00:03:46,893 --> 00:03:50,355
What do you mean “think”? You’re not sure?

56
00:03:53,441 --> 00:03:56,277
You’re pretty, everyone probably likes you.

57
00:04:09,415 --> 00:04:11,376
If you had a chance

58
00:04:11,376 --> 00:04:15,129
to have dinner with just one person in the world,

59
00:04:18,007 --> 00:04:22,470
who would you choose?

60
00:04:32,855 --> 00:04:35,233
Do you want to have dinner with me today?

61
00:04:37,193 --> 00:04:38,569
What should I do?

62
00:04:38,569 --> 00:04:41,406
I have things to do at home tonight.

63
00:04:43,032 --> 00:04:44,033
Ah…

64
00:04:46,286 --> 00:04:48,371
I retook the exam because of you.

65
00:04:49,914 --> 00:04:52,208
Why are you bringing that up now?

66
00:04:52,792 --> 00:04:53,835
And—

67
00:04:53,835 --> 00:04:55,461
You chose to retake it.

68
00:05:03,261 --> 00:05:04,595
Then…

69
00:05:04,595 --> 00:05:06,014
Do you want to eat at my place?

70
00:05:15,398 --> 00:05:16,316
Let’s go, hurry.

71
00:05:16,316 --> 00:05:17,191
Huh?

72
00:05:17,191 --> 00:05:19,569
Wait, I need to tidy this up.

73
00:05:19,569 --> 00:05:21,779
Ah, I’ll do it tomorrow.

74
00:05:21,779 --> 00:05:22,905
Let’s go.

75
00:05:25,533 --> 00:05:26,701
Come on, hurry.

76
00:05:26,701 --> 00:05:28,244
I need to finish this.

77
00:05:28,244 --> 00:05:31,456
You said you’d buy me dinner, come on.

78
00:05:56,647 --> 00:05:59,275
You remember the day I confessed before?

79
00:06:02,862 --> 00:06:04,655
Do you remember?

80
00:06:06,783 --> 00:06:09,077
You were cute back then.

81
00:06:10,870 --> 00:06:13,498
I was pretty young.

82
00:06:14,832 --> 00:06:16,584
You’re still cute.

83
00:06:17,335 --> 00:06:20,713
Do I still look like a kid to you?

84
00:06:24,675 --> 00:06:26,427
Hmm…

85
00:06:31,682 --> 00:06:34,060
You still feel like a high schooler.

86
00:07:09,137 --> 00:07:10,471
Do you still like me?

87
00:07:18,020 --> 00:07:22,483
Back then, you were emotionally unstable,

88
00:07:23,359 --> 00:07:27,905
and I was older than you, so I probably seemed impressive.

89
00:07:28,239 --> 00:07:31,117
First love at that age

90
00:07:31,117 --> 00:07:34,287
tends to get romanticized as time passes.

91
00:07:37,206 --> 00:07:39,542
So—

92
00:07:40,042 --> 00:07:41,210
Yeah?

93
00:07:42,462 --> 00:07:44,464
So what?

94
00:07:44,464 --> 00:07:46,466
We’ve only had a few glasses of wine,

95
00:07:47,467 --> 00:07:49,760
and just because I idealized things from when I was young,

96
00:07:49,760 --> 00:07:52,763
kissing a grown adult man

97
00:07:52,763 --> 00:07:54,807
is supposed to be normal?

98
00:07:57,185 --> 00:07:58,978
That’s not what I meant.

99
00:08:01,898 --> 00:08:05,109
I’ll decide my feelings myself, teacher.

100
00:08:10,823 --> 00:08:13,409
Think about it.
